INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_ARMY_NA_L0002$$, 2027, $$Army$$, $$PROC_ARMY$$, $$ARMY$$, NULL, $$2$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

Justification:
The FY 2027 budget request includes twenty-seven (27) THAAD Interceptors, Interceptor Obsolescence mitigations efforts, THAAD Ground Component Modifications, the Stockpile Reliability Program (SRP),
and AN/TPY-2 Sensors AWFG REX Redesign Kits & Secure Servers.

Previously, THAAD successfully used a "synergy" lot buy approach to THAAD Interceptor procurement. This approach entailed awarding a contract that included an option for the following FY funding. By utilizing
this approach, THAAD achieved savings in material costs in multiple FYs. This resulted in a higher Interceptor quantity buy at a lower average unit price than if the lot buys were not combined.

The Army will initiate a Multi-Year Procurement contract for THAAD Interceptors in FY27.

"Procurement Quantity" and "Flyaway Unit Cost" above represent Interceptors only, but the "Net Procurement" cost above includes the costs of all hardware. "Gross Weapon System Unit Cost" above represents
Interceptors, THAAD Mods, THAAD Launcher, and AN/TPY-2.




