 Description:
 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for M-SHORAD includes $631,114 thousand of discretionary and $80,850 thousand of mandatory for a total of $711,964 thousand.

 This funding line is directly aligned to the Army Air and Missile Defense Modernization Priority.

 SGT STOUT is an Air Defense weapon system consisting of multiple ground-to-air missile launchers, sensors, and a gun integrated on a Stryker Combat Vehicle. The SGT STOUT system provides the Army
 improved capabilities for defense of maneuver formations and other tactical echelons from adversarial low altitude air attack and surveillance. The system is in response to an adaptive suite of airborne threat
 capabilities, supported by an integrated mix of surface-to-air and surface-to-surface shooters that threaten the ability of maneuver forces to conduct operations. Specifically, maneuver formations require the air
 defense identification and defeat capabilities of the M-SHORAD system to counter to counter Fixed Wing, Rotary Wing, and Unmanned Aerial System threats.

 This system provides the capability to identify, track, and neutralize or destroy low-altitude air threats to include FW, RW, and UAS while keeping pace and surviving with the maneuver Brigades. The Army is
 currently utilizing Middle Tier Acquisition - Rapid Fielding authorities and will transition to Major Capability Acquisition at Milestone C in FY 2026." (Removes the unnecessary hyphen in Milestone C. The SGT
 STOUT program will be fielded to six SGT STOUT battalions and ITB's (Institutional Training Base). SGT STOUT will provide the long-term capability to counter a broad range of FW, RW and UAS threats.

 The total cost of the SGT STOUT Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA) Rapid Fielding (RF) effort is $1,732.5 million from FY 2024 to FY 2026, including RDT&E ($41.9M) and procurement ($1,690.6M) of SGT
 STOUT systems. The remainder of the SGT STOUT MTA RF is fully funded across the Future Years Defense Program.

 Procurement quantities for prior years and FY 2025 are incorrect. Correct Quantities are: Prior - 201, FY 2025 - 0, FY 2026 - 29, FY 2027 - 14, FY 2028 - 0, FY 2029-31 - 0




