INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_ARMY_NA_L0014$$, 2027, $$Army$$, $$PROC_ARMY$$, $$ARMY$$, NULL, $$14$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

Justification:
The FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $1,058.093 million supports the procurement of 4,824 rockets. In FY 2027, the Army will procure 2,928 Standard Unitary, 1,596 Standard AW, and 300
ER GMLRS AW in support of the Army's Total Munitions Requirement (TMR). The Army intends to convert any price advantage created through contract negotiations, other service procurement, and/or foreign
military sales to support procurement of additional GMLRS rockets.

In previous years, procurement of all GMLRS and ER-GMLRS variants was under C65404. Beginning in FY 2026, the Army established separate sub-lines for each variant to properly account for different cost,
schedule, and performance metrics.

The Army is executing procurement of missiles under a four-year Multi-Year Procurement (MYP) contract covering FY 2024 - FY 2027.

FY 2027 Advance Procurement dollars in the amount of $49.106 million procures long lead items for GMLRS production in FY 2028. Advance Procurement dollars are required to reduce production lead time of
standard range GMLRS and ER-GMLRS from 36 months to 24 months to mitigate supply chain volatility. Advance Procurement is required annually to maintain a 24-month lead time.

Funding decreased in FY 2027 due to a decrease in quantities to be procured.

The total annual production capacity is 14,004 rockets inclusive of all variants.

The Army Acquisition Objective is 140,004.

In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.




