 Description:
 Air Defense Artillery (ADA) Targets program procures target hardware and associated training devices to include scoring, payload, and ground support equipment to provide equipment to facilitate Soldier force
 on target training against drones. This training consists of Department of the Army Pamphlet (DA PAM) 350-38 (Standards in Training Commission) required gunnery tables and aerial target tracking, training, and
 scoring. Target systems are also available to support collective training exercises and Force Development Test and Experimentation (FDT&E) investigations of engagement techniques against small unmanned
 aircraft systems.
