 Description:
 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Generators And Associated Equip includes $89,073 thousand of discretionary and $40,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $129,073 thousand.

 This line provides the power generation and distribution mission critical capability that enables the Army's combat weapon systems and platforms, such as Soldier Borne Sensors, Lasers and Optics as well as
 Precision Fires & Air Missile Defense systems and Battalion and above Command Posts.

 The Generator and associated equipment funding lines are structured to support the Small Tactical Electric Power (STEP) that provides 2-3kW, Advanced Medium Mobile Power Sources (AMMPS) that provides
 5-60kW, Large Tactical Power System (LTPS) that provides 500kW, and Deployable Power Generation and Distribution System (DPGDS) Power Unit (PU) that provides 900kW of tactical electric power.

 The Generators and Associated Equipment funding line also supports power distribution and storage. This includes Power Distribution Illumination Systems Electrical (PDISE) which is associated with AMMPS
 and Prime Power Distribution System (PPDS) which is associated with DPGDS.

 These programs collectively provide a new, modern family of generators and distribution systems satisfying critical user requirements.

 Tactical Electric Power (TEP) systems will support the joint force and will provide an interface for future On-board Vehicle and Hybrid Power systems.

 Power Distribution Illumination Systems Electrical (PDISE) transmits electrical power efficiently from the point of power generation to the point of need. PDISE links the generator to Command and Control, Air
 & Missile Defense, Long Range Precision Fires, and Combat Support/Combat Service Support systems. PDISE components are man-portable and safe for all weather operations to protect Soldiers from electric
 shock. PDISE is a reliable, quick to assemble, modular designed power distribution equipment that is critical to deploying power networks. PDISE is compatible with AMMPS generator sets from 5 to 60kW.
 PDISE includes M200, M100, M40, M60 and M46 which are required associated items of equipment for standard military generators.

 M200 Army Acquisition Objective (AAO) = 395; M100 AAO = 2,848; M60 AAO = 6,524; M40 AAO = 5,980; M46 AAO = 17,591.

 Prime Power Distribution Systems (PPDS) will resolve power distribution capability gaps in the prime power, medium voltage (4160 Volts Alternating Current (VAC)) arena. Current systems require modernization
 to support the 249th Engineer Battalion (Prime Power) and its National Response Framework (NRF) mission, providing DoW support to civil defense and Force Provider Expeditionary (FPE) contingency base


