Justification:
FY 2027 base procurement dollars of $65.020 million support the following:
-------------------------------------
Collective Protection (M01006):

FY 2027 base procurement dollars of $22.276 million supports the procurement of Line Item Numbers (LINS) that support the 32-bed Hospital Unit Base, the 24-bed Surgical Augment, the 32-bed Medical
Augment, and the 60-bed Intensive Care Ward Chemically Protected Deployable Medical Systems (CP DEPMEDS) configuration. These CP DEPMEDS sets will be configured to match the new force design
update configuration of Army field hospitals. P-40 Resource Summary quantities identify the number of complete systems; P-5 Cost Elements quantities identify LINS that makeup the complete 240-bed system.
-------------------------------------
Radiological Detection System (RDS) (M01280)

FY 2027 base procurement dollars of $12.166 million will support the procurement and fielding of 1,565 configuration one RDS's as the first Joint solution to provide the Warfighter with the net-ready capability to
measure alpha, beta, gamma, neutron, and low energy x-rays. RDS incorporates geolocation data- Global Positioning System (GPS) interface capability, Network Ready (NetReady) data and lessons learned
from Operation TOMODACHI which includes common measurements, common equipment, and adequate sensitivity. In addition to procurement of systems, FY 2027 includes funding calibration equipment to
support the RDS.

Unit pricing of Configurations varies by fiscal year based on quantities of systems being procured across the Joint Services, not only the Army.
---------------------------------------
Nuclear Biological Chemical Reconnaissance Vehicle Sensor Suite Upgrade (NBCRV SSU) (M02241)

FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $18.250 million supports the procurement of 10 Unmanned Aerial System (UAS) Chemical, Biological, Radiological, Nuclear (CBRN) Kits and associated
engineering and logistics costs to support production and fielding. P-40 quantities in prior years and FY 2025 are incorrect; please see P-5 for correct quantities.
---------------------------------------
Joint Personal Dosimeter Individual (JPD-I) (W43487):

FY 2027 base procurement dollars of $6.368 million supports the procurement of 8,510 Joint Personal Dosimeter Individual (JPD-I) sensors to provide a component to passively record and retrieve a Service
member's radiation exposure, as well as associated logistics, systems engineering, and fielding support. P-40 quantities in FY 2025 are incorrect; please see P-5 for correct quantities.


