 Description:
 This funding line is directly aligned to the Army's Network Modernization Strategy Line of Effort (LOE) #1, Unified Network.

 The Ground Soldier Systems funding line known as Nett Warrior (NW) procures commercial End User Devices and supporting equipment that provide the dismounted combat leader with integrated mission
 command and situational awareness during Large-Scale Combat Operations (LSCO) operations. The NW system provides operators real-time information on friendly positions, navigational data, map imagery,
 enemy activity/movement information and other mission related graphics. NW uses Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS) and Non-Developmental communications equipment to create a robust and flexible
 Secure but Unclassified - Encrypted (SBU-E) Network Baseline that enables faster and more accurate decision-making during combat operations at the tactical level. NW also procures supporting power
 systems to deliver power requirements in the expeditionary environment. NW systems fielded across all formations in a Brigade Combat Team (BCT) and provide voice, video and data exchange with formation
 headquarters at battalion and higher levels to achieve a single Common Operating Picture (COP). This COP enables faster, more flexible information exchanges with Joint, Coalition and Partner forces. NW is
 a critical Transformation in Contact (TiC) dismounted capability supporting Army Modernization priorities by providing a dismounted common computational platform and enabling a single point of integration and
 interface for Soldier-borne systems to facilitate data sharing. NW fielding equipment supports Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2), accelerated Armored Brigade Combat Teams (ABCTs), and Mobile
 Brigade Combat Teams (MBCT) transformation. Funding in this project aligns with the Army's priorities in support of TiC.

 The AAO for NW is 80,740.
