 Justification:
 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $115.535 million supports the following STE signature efforts: Reconfigurable Virtual Collective Trainers (RVCT), Training Simulation Software/Training
 Management Tools (TSS/TMT), One World Terrain (OWT), and STE Live.

 NA2012: FY 2027 STE Live base procurement dollars in the amount of $79.607 million will procure Force on Force engagement types to fund continued production and fielding of STE Live Inc 1 products for
 JRTC and NTC and support the initial production of STE Live capabilities to the Joint Multinational Readiness Center (JMRC), and Joint Pacific Multinational Readiness Center (JPMRC). Efforts will promote
 synergies between the training and testing enablers to improve product integration, deployment, and cyber activities, and to promote re-use of common assets and services to meet Army modernization priorities.

 NA2013: No funding budgeted in FY 2027 for Soldier Virtual Trainer.

 NA2014: FY 2027 RVCT base procurement dollars in the amount of $1.587 million will provide for the tech refresh of the Air Platform's Helmet Mounted Display.

 NA2015: FY 2027 OWT base procurement dollars in the amount of $10.218 million will procure new terrain in support of the Synthetic Training Environment (STE) Family of Programs (FoP), extensive data
 acquisition for Next Generation Constructive (NGC), and terrain refreshes to ensure current and accurate terrain data. Additionally, hardware procurement and refreshes will support NGC's growing processing
 and storage demands and maintain system performance and compatibility. Additionally, base funding will enable the ability to deploy, operate, and secure OWT capabilities in accordance with OSW and Army
 Digital Engineering and Software Modernization Strategies. Efforts will promote synergies between the training and testing enablers to improve product integration, deployment, and cyber activities, and to
 promote re-use of common assets and services to meet Army modernization priorities.

 NA2016: FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $24.123 million supports the following efforts:

 STE Software (TSS/TMT) base procurement dollars in the amount of $24.123 million will procure hardware, spares, and associated fielding activities at eight (8) locations. Additionally, base funding will enable
 the ability to deploy, operate, and secure STE Software capabilities in accordance with OSW and Army Digital Engineering and Software Modernization Strategies. Efforts will promote synergies between the
 training and testing enablers to improve product integration, deployment, and cyber activities, and to promote re-use of common assets and services to meet Army modernization priorities.

 Funding was transferred from Other Procurement, Army Synthetic Training Environment in the amount of $19.337 million to Operation and Maintenance, Army SAG 121 Force Readiness Operations Support to
 properly align funding in accordance with current Army guidance on procurement of software licenses.



