 Justification:
 FY 2027 procurement funding in the amount of $137.271 million provides funding for ICIDS (MA0781) in the amount of $31.323 million; CIDS (MA0782) in the amount of $22.788 million; and Other Physical
 Security Measures Equipment (MA0783) in the amount of $83.160 million.

 MA0781 - ($31.323 million)

 PEO Intelligence, Electronic Warfare and Sensors (PEO IEW&S) - ($21.143 million) - FY 2027 procurement dollars provides installation of ICIDS at multiple OPMG prioritized locations; and Windows 11
 conversions for non-compliant ICIDS. Funding supports a balanced investment strategy for the Army approved force structure and requirements. All ICIDS quantities and funding are for Active Components.

 Other Organizations

 US Army Material Command - ($0.032 million) - FY 2027 funding to support intrusion detection systems for construction at new facilities.

 US Army Corps of Engineers (USACE) - ($0.989 million) - FY 2027 funding to support intrusion detection systems for construction at new facilities.

 US Army Central Command (USARCENT) - ($3.388 million) - FY 2027 funding to support intrusion detection systems for construction at new facilities to support the enduring requirement for Operation Spartan
 Shield.

 US Army Installation Management Command (IMCOM) ($4.894 million) - Physical Security and Intrusion Detection System Equipment Modernization

 Army Corrections Command ($0.877 million) - Physical Security and Intrusion Detection System Equipment Modernization

 MA0782 - ($22.788 million)

 OFC, SEC OF THE ARMY, Resources Services Washington (RSW) ($14.474 million) - Procurement for CIDS (MA0782) procurement dollars supports procuring 389 sites and 11 Ammunition Supply Points to
 modernized integrated physical security equipment for intrusion detection and assessment, access control, electronic surveillance and force protection equipment at existing National Guard Facilities and some
 Active Army sites. Funding provides security measures for conventional arms, ammunition and explosive storage facilities, sensitive compartment information facilities and other areas containing assets for which
 policy requires Intrusion Detection Systems. Risks and vulnerabilities are minimized by providing Commanders with the appropriate levels of protection through the use of available technology to safeguard
 personnel and Army assets. Funding supports a balanced investment strategy for the Army's approved force structure and requirements. All quantities and funding are for Active, USAR and ARNG Components.


