 Justification:
 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $41.358 million supports the following efforts:

 M15561: There is no funding request for this program in FY 2027.

 MA4501:
 Modification Items #1 Material Handling Equipment (MHE) Technical Insertion (PEO CS & CSS) - FY 2027 Base procurement dollars for PdM EMSE Material Handling Equipment (MHE) of $23.671 million
 provides 36 each modernized Rough Terrain Container Handlers (RTCH) and all associated program support costs to support Base requirements.

 Modification Item #2 Construction Equipment (CE) Tech Insertion (PEO CS & CSS) - There is no funding request for this modification item in FY 2027.

 Modification Item #3 Army Watercraft Systems (PEO CS & CSS) - FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $7.911 million supports pier side and shipyard modifications of all outstanding and
 emerging Engineering Change Proposals (ECP) and Modification Work Orders (MWO) across the watercraft fleet. Application of ECPs/MWOs will regain fleet configuration control, improve operational readiness,
 correct safety and regulatory deficiencies, comply with changing federal statutory and regulatory mandates, comply with safety of life at sea (SOLAS) requirements, command, control, communications,
 computers, combat systems, intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance (C5ISR), and comply with all necessary environmental requirements. Funding also supports the Integration and installation of autonomy
 capability when technologically is available, Program Management/Matrix Support, upgrades/modifications to Army Watercraft Systems which are completed as required to resolve any survivability / force
 protection - lethal and non-lethal Escalation of Force (EoF) issues, and technical insertions. Program Management/Matrix Support includes Program Management and System Engineering; Logistics oversight
 required to manage the program and provide contractor oversight. The funds are to procure and install non-LIN equipment. .

 Modification Item #4 M139 Volcano Mine Dispensing System (JPEO A&A) - FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $1.000 million provides for modifications of 1 Volcano Mine Dispensing system to
 support fielding for identified shortages. Also, funding continues technical efforts required to address Air Mounting Kit technical data deficiencies prior to starting Air Mounting Kit repairs.


