INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_ARMY_NA_L0122$$, 2027, $$Army$$, $$PROC_ARMY$$, $$ARMY$$, NULL, $$122$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 FY 2027 Base dollars in the amount of $362.356 million supports the following projects in accordance with the OIB Modernization Implementation Plan:

 ------------

 $139.000M - Digital Transformation (AMC): Leverages advanced technologies including Digital Twins and predictive maintenance to optimize workflows, enhance decision-making, and drive measurable
 improvements in throughput and readiness across the OIB enterprise.

 ------------

 $80.000M - Industrial Control Network (ICN) Completion (AMC): Establishes a secure, interconnected ICN across all OIB GOGO sites to enable robust connectivity and seamless data transport for all operational
 technology (OT).

 ------------

 $71.716M - Component Remanufacturing Facility (CRF) Equipment (TACOM/ANAD): Provides essential production equipment for the new CRF at Anniston Army Depot funded under the Reconciliation Act to
 accelerate the overhaul of over 4,600 components for 19 vehicle platforms.

 ------------

 $32.000M - Advanced Manufacturing / Non-Recurring Engineering (AMC): Procures industrial-grade metal and polymer 3D printing systems for Rock Island Arsenal, Tobyhanna Army Depot, and Letterkenny
 Army Depot to enable the on-demand production of airworthy and battle-ready components addressing critical supply chain vulnerabilities.

 ------------

 $26.720M - MicroElectronics (ME) Upgrades (CECOM/TYAD): Funds facilities upgrades and equipment at to create new production lines that will significantly increase the annual throughput of Circuit Card
 Assemblies (CCAs).

 ------------

 $7.000M - Innovation Hub (JMC/BGAD): Establishes a state-of-the-art facility dedicated to advancing Unmanned/Uncrewed Systems (UxS), providing critical capabilities in prototyping, manufacturing, and
 testing.

