 Description:
 Funding has partially been realigned out of this line to support the Army's Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) initiative.

 BU8100 COTS Communication Equipment (CE) procures non-developmental items (NDI) and services in support of the Army's Network Modernization Strategy by providing interoperability and continuity
 through the procurement of tactical communication enhancement equipment, ancillaries, and related services. Components supported under COTS CE include but are not limited to: HF radios, Link 16 radios,
 communication gateways, line-of-sight (LOS) radios, and beyond line-of-sight (BLOS) radios. These items provide resilient software-defined communication systems and operational utility and adaptability
 through simplified and protected communications.

 Contingency Communications (B98115) procures, integrates, and fields assured multi-path communications for senior Department of War leaders while traveling in different platforms. Integration of commercial
 off-the-shelf (COTS) SATCOM/Cellular Internet communications to enable secure communications and TS/SCI voice teleconferences.

 This funding supports the Army's Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) initiative to modernize Command and Control (C2) systems.

 BU8100 COTS Communication Equipment (CE) is the Parent Line to Communications Gateways (B98111), Networked Radios Planner (B98112), Cross Domain Solution PEO C3T (B98113), Contingency
 Communications (B98115), High Frequency Radios (B98120) and Low Cost Tactical Radio (B08105).

 In FY 2027 funds have been realigned from B08105 Low-Cost Tactical Radio Replacement and B98120 High Frequency Radios to SSN B11500 C2 Transport. Networked Radios Planner (B98112) and Cross
 Domain Solution PEO C3T (B98113) have been realigned to SSN B11400 C2 Infrastructure.
