 Description:
 ADVANCED SITUATIONAL AWARENESS SYSTEMS (SSN K81500)
 This funding line is directly aligned to the Army Modernization Priorities in support of situational awareness for the Dismounted Soldier. Advanced situational awareness systems are a fight, train, and rehearse
 capability through a system of systems approach. The funding line provides the Dismounted Soldier with enhanced situational awareness capabilities through night vision, digital sensors and integrated mission
 command and control. Advanced situational awareness systems provide operators real-time information on friendly and enemy activity, navigational data and map imagery, and other mission-related applications.
 These systems enable Human Machine Integration (HMI) with other Army-fielded platforms through a common architecture optimizing extensibility.

 SOLDIER BORNE MISSION COMMAND (SBMC) SYSTEM (SSN K91511)
 The Soldier Borne Mission Command (SBMC) system converges capabilities onto a single digital architecture optimized to emerging modular technologies while backwards compatible with fielded equipment. At
 end state, the SBMC system provides the Army with an optimized fused digital awareness system that shows real-time operational information, enhanced visual situational awareness and on-body compute to
 support extensibility.

 ENHANCED NIGHT VISION GOGGLE - BINOCULAR (ENVG-B) (SSN K81514)
 The Enhanced Night Vision Goggle- Binocular (ENVG-B) system is a modular helmet-mounted, passive electro-optical fused sensor imaging device in a binocular configuration. The system integrates dual
 Image Intensification (I2) sensors with the thermal sensor imagery into a single viewing display. The thermal sensor provides the Soldier with the capability to rapidly detect and recognize human-sized targets
 in adverse weather, obscurants and in varying light conditions. The dual I2 sensors provide the Soldier with depth perception for ease of low-light level maneuvers and the ability to detect rifle-mounted aiming
 lights to engage targets. The ENVG-B can also be operated in a monocular configuration by moving one of the two individually rotating monoculars. The ENVG-B has a near infrared (NIR) emitting light source
 that provides illumination for close-up viewing. The ENVG-B mounts on the Army's combat helmet. The ENVG-B operates with the Family of Weapon Sights- Individual (FWS-I) through the Intra-Soldier Wireless
 (ISW) network to provide passive targeting, which is the capability to view the boresighted/zeroed weapon sight reticle in the ENVG-B display, enabling the Soldier to accurately engage targets without having
 to bring the weapon to eye level and without the use of active lasers, all while remaining in defilade. The soldier can also view the Nett Warrior Augmented Reality (AR) navigational, targeting, and situational
 graphics in the ENVG-B display. This funding line is directly aligned to the Army Soldier Lethality Modernization Priority in support of situational awareness for the Close Area Combat Force.

 SOLDIER POWER (SSN K81512)
 Soldier Power funding line procures the Universal Battery Charger (UBC), power and data managing/distribution devices, cutting-edge energy storage solutions (Conformal Wearable Batteries (CWB)), and power
 scavenging devices. These capabilities fill the power and energy gaps created by the increase in mission essential, Soldier portable power consumers, such as heads up displays, situational awareness displays,


