INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_ARMY_NA_L0034$$, 2027, $$Army$$, $$PROC_ARMY$$, $$ARMY$$, NULL, $$34$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

Justification:
FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $145.507 million supports the below programs:

COMSEC Cryptographic Systems (CCS) / (B96002): FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $55.638 million supports procurements to upgrade to the NSA directed Cryptographic Modernization 2
(CM2) and NSA High Assurance Internet Protocol Encryption (HAIPE) Binding Operational Directive (BOD). The funding supports the procurement and fielding of modern In-Line Network Encryptors (INE), Link
family of Encryptors, and Secure Voice (SV) devices at multiple price points to provide cryptographic equipment that receive key through fill devices and allow for secure communication through Army devices
such as radios and satellite terminals. This effort is a key enabler of the Army's Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) initiative to modernize Command and Control (C2) systems.

Army Key Management Infrastructure (AKMI) / (B96004): FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $28.266 million supports the procurement, fielding, depot support for Key Management
Infrastructure (KMI) Management Client Node (MGC), Simple Key Loader (SKL), Next Generation Load Device - Small (NGLD-S), and Automated Communication Engineering Software (ACES) enabling the
Army to manage, control, plan, and distribute electronic key and related products to the approximately 1.5 million End Cryptographic Units (ECU)s necessary to communicate and distribute data on the Army's
tactical through strategic networks. The end state for the Army is to leverage AKMI capabilities (Over the Network Keying (OTNK) software (Intermediary Application (iApp)), Delivery Only Client (DOC), Client
Host Only (CHO) to increase automation, reduce soldier oversight, manage, and deliver key products to the tactical edge up through strategic ECUs.

Next Generation Load Device - Medium (NGLD-M) / (B96016): FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $61.603 million supports the procurement, fielding, depot support for Next Generation Load
Device - Medium (NGLD-M) which replaces the legacy Simple Key Loader (SKL). NGLD-M adds capability of cryptographic re-programmability, Over the Network Keying (OTNK), and is upgradable to NSA's
Cryptographic Modernization 2 (CM2) algorithms. Funding supports the NGLD-M procurement effort for two vendors. NGLD-M program realized a delay in FY 2025 and procurement efforts started in FY 2026

Modernization of fill devices are supported through this funding line. It provides government and contractor engineering support, Production and Post Deployment Systems Support, system technical and software
support of the AKMI components. The Production and Post Deployment Systems Support contract supports AKMI components, operational support for deployed and sustaining forces, technical engineering &
support, associated government and contractor engineering support, and the development and updating of Web based training for AKMI components to augment in-class delta and sustainment training.

In accordance with section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110 - 181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.




