 Justification:
 No funding is requested in FY 2027.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for this Procurement MD65 Defense of Guam includes $11.351 million of discretionary and $56.500 million of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $67.851 million.

 FY 2026 Procurement includes the procurement of ancillary equipment and components, which are the cooperative engagement capability system.

 FY 2025 Procurement included the material purchases to support the Defense of Guam architecture to support the initial deployment on the island in early FY 2025. Components included:
 - Ancillary equipment to include inertial navigation system tech refresh and spares.
 - Aegis Weapons System components to support Integrated Air and Missile Defense delivery in CY 2032 to include additional fire control system; identification, friend or foe system equipment; and spares.
 - C4I to include shipping containers and spares.

 The above procurement quantity reflects procurement of a single overarching Aegis Guam System made up of multiple weapon system components. "Procurement Quantity" represents the Aegis Guam System
 that consists of Aegis Weapon System Equipment, Ancillary Equipment, C4I, and VLS.




