 Justification:
 PROPONENT/MISSION IT-MCA/PHYSICAL RELOCATION (B31510):

 FY 2027 procurement dollars in the amount of $56.640 million support PROPONENT/MISSION IT-MCA/PHYSICAL RELOCATION with procurement of commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) end-user devices
 (including telephones, soft phones, computing devices), associated licensing, secure data switches and gateways for classified and unclassified connectivity. It also supports information systems for classrooms,
 computers for traditional business users and Warfighters, teleconferencing systems, display/knowledge walls, secure telephone equipment, and physical plant infrastructure to support those information system
 assets. Procurements include network infrastructure engineering, acquisition, installation, security, and quality assurance to support the planning, design, implementation, and completion of a multitude of MCA
 and SRM projects. Installation of the Mission Unique Equipment (MUE)/end user equipment is dependent upon construction timelines as it is the final phase of an MCA or SRM project. MUE is required to
 ensure new/renovated buildings are complete and usable, mission capable and ready for unit/Soldier occupancy. The primary contributor to the increase in FY 2027 is the Mission Unique IT funding for EUCOM
 Headquarters. Specific breakdown of all Base projects listed below:

 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $2.506 million supports INSCOM MUE such as switches, virtual desktop systems, computers, monitors, hard and soft phones, printers, large screen displays,
 cameras, video codecs, microphones, speakers, and other supporting IT equipment.

 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $17.155 million supports ARCYBER MUE such as routers, switches, virtual desktop systems, computers, data storage, hard and soft phones, cabling,
 cameras, sound and video mixers, display panels, speakers, and other IT equipment.

 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $30.753 million supports EUCOM MUE such as routers, switches, virtual desktop systems, computers, data storage, hard and soft phones, cabling, cameras,
 sound and video mixers, display panels, speakers, and other IT equipment.

 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $0.346 million supports AMC MUE such as switches, virtual desktop systems, computers, data storage, phones, cabling, cameras, sound and video mixers,
 display panels, speakers, and other IT equipment.

 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $1.970 million supports USFK MUE such as routers, switches, virtual desktop systems, computers, data storage, hard and soft phones, cabling, cameras,
 sound and video mixers, display panels, speakers, and other IT equipment.

 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $3.206 million supports USARPAC MUE such as switches, virtual desktop systems, computers, hard and soft phones, cabling, cameras, sound and video
 mixers, display panels, speakers, and other supporting IT equipment.




