 Description:
 This funding line supports Army 2030/2040 efforts and implements the HQDA G6 Infrastructure modernization priorities to achieve an Army Global Unified Network (Army's Software Defined Network (SDN)
 Solution), Global Secure Network (GSN), and Unified Network (UN) utilizing Zero Trust based principles.

 The Enterprise Transport Modernization (ETM) Program approved in 2024, provides a comprehensive approach to lifecycle network modernization for the U.S. Army's communications infrastructure to support
 Multi-Domain Operations (MDO) and enhance Mission Command from Afar across all components Active Army, Army National Guard, and Army Reserve. ETM consists of four key capabilities: Installation
 Campus Area Network (ICAN) Modernization, Inside Plant (ISP), Outside Plant (OSP), and Army Enterprise Transport (AET). ICAN Modernization includes upgrading network equipment such as switches,
 routers, and fiber optic cables to provide robust Internet Protocol (IP) connectivity across Army installations and enable wireless technologies such as WiFi, 5G, and FutureG. ISP and OSP efforts modernize
 internal infrastructure (e.g., racks, power, HVAC) and external infrastructure (e.g., fiber optic cabling) to ensure secure, reliable connectivity. Last, AET serves as the Army's Gateway to enhance connection
 between local users and the Department of War Information Network (DOWIN-A) Wide Area Network (WAN).

 ETM provides the necessary network infrastructure to enable Unified Capabilities (UC), Regional Service Nodes (RSN), Joint Information Environment (JIE), Synthetic Training Environments (STE), and
 decommissions outdated systems such as Time Division Multiplexers (TDM) to ensure the Army's communication systems meets modern operational demands securely.

 Modernizing the Army's communication infrastructure will enable a Unified Network to support a range of critical capabilities, including cloud-based services, large-scale communications systems, and
 Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2). The goal is to reduce management and maintenance costs, improve the Army's operational efficiency, and increase the reliability and security of Army
 communications, both within the continental United States (CONUS) and Outside the Continental United States (OCONUS).

 These efforts align with the broader strategic Army Global Unified Network (AGUN) effort, Cryptographic Hardware Modernization, and efforts to support mobility and wireless communications. The ETM program
 represents a critical investment in enabling the Army to remain secure and capable of executing multi-domain operations effectively.

 B00540 / I3MP-SWA: I3MP-SWA delivers comprehensive lifecycle network modernization to refresh the existing legacy network's infrastructure, voice, video, data, and Mission Command from Afar capabilities.
 I3MP-SWA delivers capabilities associated with the Global Secure Network (GSN), including Secure-Consolidated Security Suite (S-CSS) hardware & integration, Multiple Independent Levels of Security (MILS)
 hardware and integration, and End User Devices (EUDs). I3MP-SWA delivers capabilities associated with Army Global Unified Network (AGUN) (Army's SDN Solution), including Consolidated Security Suite
 (CSS) hardware and integration, SDLAN hardware and integration, and SDN device provisioning.


