 Justification:
 BU0510 / I3MP-Europe:
 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $8.374 million enables the Project Manager to expand the Army Global Unified Network (AGUN) (Army's SDN Solution) capabilities in Europe. Funding
 provides the hardware and integration for the global orchestrator, regional controllers, Software Defined-Wide Area Network (SD-WAN) Edge sites, Software Defined-Local Area Network (SD-LAN) orchestrator,
 Next Generation Firewall (NGFW) with Secure Access Service Edge (SASE) capabilities, remote access capabilities, and the cybersecurity accreditation required to achieve Authority to Operate (ATO)
 associated with the AGUN capability.

 BU0520 / I3MP-Pacific:
 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $8.069 million enables the Project Manager to expand the AGUN (Army's SDN Solution) in the Pacific. Funding provides the hardware and integration for
 the global orchestrator, regional controllers, SD-WAN Edge sites, SD-LAN orchestrator, NGFW with SASE capabilities, remote access capabilities, and the cybersecurity accreditation required to achieve ATO
 associated with the AGUN capability.

 BU0530 / I3MP-CONUS:
 FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $308.388 million enables the Project Manager to deliver comprehensive lifecycle network modernization (COMPMOD) globally to multiple locations including
 Fort Leavenworth, Letterkenny, Carlisle, RRMC, Tobyhanna AD, Detroit Arsenal, MOTSU, Pine Bluff, McCoy, Stuttgart, McAlester, Hunter-Liggett, Dugway PG, Schofield, Kwajalein, Fort Shafter, Pohakuloa,
 Kilauea, Yuma. COMPMOD will modernize, expand, enhance, and upgrade IT infrastructure, IT systems, IT support systems, communications systems, and associated infrastructure, hardware, and software.
 COMPMOD includes modernizing the Installation Campus Area Network (ICAN) consisting of network equipment (e.g. switches, routers, fiber optic cable, wireless connection devices, copper cable) and
 associated transport on each Army installation that provides Internet Protocol (IP) connectivity to the users; Inside Plant (ISP), which includes infrastructure modernization (e.g. racks, power & grounding, HVAC,
 cable management); Outside Plant (OSP), which supports the ICAN's outside portion of the communication infrastructure and includes installing fiber optic cabling and associated accessories between networked
 buildings; the Army's DOWIN-A gateway, which connects local users to the DOWIN-A Wide Area Network (WAN); and voice modernization, which includes Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) and other voice
 services to installations and tenants. Additionally, the funding allows the PM to deliver and implement hardware and software for Multiple Independent Levels of Security (MILS) and the SIPR-Consolidated
 Security Suite (S- CSS) capability associated with the Global Secure Network (GSN) nodes in Germany and Korea; deliver and integrate Multi-Site Connectivity (MSC) capability hardware and software forming
 outlying Army organization connections to the GSN nodes while enabling the divestment of expensive Type 1 NSA encryption devices; and End User Device (EUD) hardware and software for CONUS GSN end
 users.

 B00540 / I3MP-SWA: FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $1.961 million delivers and implements hardware and software for Multiple Independent Levels of Security (MILS) and the SIPR-
 Consolidated Security Suite (S- CSS) capability associated with the Global Secure Network (GSN) nodes.


