Justification:
NXGBCC - FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $2.862 million supports deploying, training, and fielding of Next Generation Biometric Collection Capability (NXGBCC). Funding also supports the
procurement of 151 devices.

CIHEP -A - FY 2027 base procurement dollars in the amount of $3.052 million supports procurement of 18 kits comprised of Commercial off the Shelf (COTS) and Government off the Shelf (GOTS) components
for fielding.

This program is included in the OPA Budget Line Consolidation. In FY 2025, the CI/HUMINT EQUIPMENT PROGRAM-ARMY (CIHEP-A) (B75200) and BIOMETRICS AUTOMATED TOOLSET - ARMY (BAT-A)
(BK5300) were consolidated into the COLLECTION CAPABILITY (B87000) program.

In accordance with section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110 - 181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.




