 Description:
 The Counter-Rocket, Artillery and Mortar (C-RAM) Enhancements line (H30504) provides the Land-based Phalanx Weapon System (LPWS) C-RAM capability to the Indirect Fire Protection Capability (IFPC)/
 Avenger Battalions, 5-5 and 2-44 Air Defense Artillery. The LPWS consists of a trailer-mounted, high rate of fire 20mm Gatling gun guided by input from its integrated search and tracking radar and Forward
 Looking Infrared receiver. It includes two 60 kW generators and a Local Control Station, also mounted on the trailer, as well as a Remote Control Station. The LPWS protects high value ground assets from
 incoming munitions, such as RAM, as well as unmanned aerial systems (UAS).
