Justification:
FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $8.696 million supports the procurement, fielding and new equipment training of 647 FWS-I systems, as well as the procurement of required spares and
ancillary items that support fielding.

FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $5.109 million supports the procurement, fielding and new equipment training of 51 FWS-S systems, as well as the procurement of required spares and
ancillary items that support fielding.

FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $1.535 million supports the prioritized fielding of STORM II systems to Snipers, Mortar, Institutional Training Requirements, USASOC and Air Defense
Dismounted authorizations. Also funds the prime contractor to provide Interim Contractor Maintenance Support, track potential parts obsolescence, track trends in field usage and repair data, conduct annual
reliability testing and, if required, make updates to the system.

In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.




