 Justification:
 FY 2027 Base funding in the amount of $84.134 million supports the procurement of seventy-nine (79) 3GEN FLIR B-Kits and the associated systems engineering and program management support costs.

 The increase in quantities of 3GEN FLIR from 48 in FY 2025 and FY 2026 (which is the minimum sustaining rate) to 79 in FY2027 is directly tied to the quantity requirement of meeting the host platform's
 requirements. For FY 2027, the planned host platform is XM30.

 Note: There is a 24-month lead time for 3GEN FLIR based on the material and manufacturing complexity. The 3GEN FLIR quantities increase to 79 units in FY 2027 is directly driven by the production schedule
 of the XM30 host platform to ensure that 3GEN FLIR B-Kits are available for integration into the host platform.




