INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_ARMY_NA_L0065$$, 2027, $$Army$$, $$PROC_ARMY$$, $$ARMY$$, NULL, $$65$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

Justification:
AD0511 / C-SUAS FIXED: The FY 2027 request will procure additional Joint and Army C-sUAS capabilities for Homeland and Specified Fixed Sites (HSFS), for self-protection against small UAS threats, and will
support upgrade of current HSFS sites to a heavy configuration, as well as providing obsolescence mitigation, sustainment spares, fielding, and Integrated Logistics Support (ILS) efforts.

AD0512 / C-SUAS OPERATIONAL: The FY 2027 request will support procurement, integration, and fielding of capabilities for C-UAS Batteries, including expeditionary and mobile platforms and sensors to
enable self-protection for critical assets, facilities, and infrastructure. It also supports procurement of additional mobile C-sUAS single vehicles and additional mobile sensor systems, to replace the dual vehicle
systems fielded in support of the initial C-UAS Battery.

AD0513 / C-SUAS GROUND READINESS: The FY 2027 request will provide ILS in support of Family of Counter-Unmanned Aircraft Systems (FoCUS) procured in prior years, to mitigate force protection
capability gaps in countering UAS threats to personnel, facilities, and infrastructure in CONUS and OCONUS locations.

AD0514 / DIRECTED ENERGY (DE): The FY 2027 request will produce up to two (2) Enduring High Energy Laser (HEL) systems based on the Army's Enduring HEL Modular Open Systems Approach (MOSA)
architecture.

AD0515 / C-SUAS LCHR: The FY 2027 request will procure 12 expeditionary launcher systems and 10 mobile launcher systems for one Army C-UAS Battery.

AD0516 / C-SUAS EFFR (EFFECTOR): The FY 2027 request will procure 800 ea. kinetic, 29 ea. non-kinetic, and 24 ea. Next Generation C-UAS Missile (NGCM) interceptor All Up Rounds for a total of 853
interceptors.

K00517 / C-SUAS SLDR COMMON: The FY 2027 request will procure and field C-sUAS capabilities for operations at Squad and individual Soldier levels, to provide dismounted, handheld, and wearable systems
for self-protection against Groups 1 & 2 UAS threats. This is not a new start in FY 2027.

K00518 / C-SUAS UNIT CMN: The FY 2027 request will procure and field C-sUAS capabilities for Brigade and below elements, to provide self-protection against Groups 1 & 2 UAS threats; convoy defense; and
defense of critical assets, formations, facilities, and infrastructure. This is not a new start in FY 2027.
